50|$|The entire {{concept of}} {{business}} continuity {{is based on}} the identification of all business functions within an organization, and then assigning a level of importance to each business function. A business impact analysis is the primary tool for gathering this information and assigning criticality, <b>recovery</b> <b>point</b> <b>objectives,</b> and <b>recovery</b> time objectives, and is therefore part of the basic foundation of business continuity.|$|R
