50|$|Mirroring is {{typically}} only synchronous. Synchronous writing typically achieves a <b>recovery</b> <b>point</b> <b>objective</b> (RPO) of zero lost data. Asynchronous replication can achieve an RPO {{of just a}} few seconds while the remaining methodologies provide an RPO of a few minutes to perhaps several hours.|$|E
